      "writtenOn": "2021-03-11T02:35:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "validateInvocationToken may return an appstatus-annotated error: \nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/resultdb/internal/services/recorder/invocation.go;l\u003d97?q\u003dvalidateInvocationToken\n\nan attempt to appstatus-annotate an error that is already appstatus-annotated, will result in a panic. Thus it is not sfe.\n\nfunctions that *may* return an appstatusa-annotated error should say that in the comment, e.g. https://source.chromium.org/search?q\u003d%2F%2F.%2Bappstatus%20-f:appstatus%20lang:go%20f:luci",
