      "side": 1,
      "message": "https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/resultdb/internal/services/recorder/invocation.go;l\u003d97?q\u003dvalidateInvocationToken\n\nThe linked function is mutateInvocation(), not validateInvocationToken().\nAlso, neither of validateInvocationToken [1] nor TokenKind.Validate [2] claims that they may return an appstatus annotated error.\n\n[1]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/resultdb/internal/services/recorder/invocation.go;l\u003d70-75\n[2]: https://source.chromium.org/chromium/infra/infra/+/master:go/src/go.chromium.org/luci/server/tokens/tokens.go;l\u003d133-142\n\nI can still add the check of `if appstatus.Get(err)`, whether validateInvocationToken() may return an appstatus annotated error or not, but as I mentioned, if we ask business logic to add such checks blindly, then appstatus should provide an helper function to make the check easier, I think. WDYT?",
